14/3/2022, 3:25â€¯p.â€¯m. - Tomi Guell: como hacer que nuestros recursos rindan lo mejor posible?
se da el segundo aspecto que es optar para repartir nuestros recursos para satisfacer al maximo posible nuestras necesidades; Cuando estos recursos no alcanzan para lograr el 
objetivo aparece el problema denominado escasez.
Si fuera una situacion del individuo, la opcion estaria en como utilizar el ingreso(Producto del salario, o de la ganancia, de un prestamo o de un regalo o ganancia
de una loteria) 
Pero la escasez tambien se presenta en las decisiones empresarias: Voy a producir un bien u otro tipo de bien?;Debo emplear mas trabajadores o recurro a maquinas roboticas?
La escasez tambien aparece en las decisiones de gobierno: Invierto mas en edcucacion y menos en seguridad?, Como repartiremos el presupuesto Nacional?

14/3/2022, 3:39â€¯p.â€¯m. - Tomi Guell: como hacer que nuestros recursos rindan lo mejor posible?
se da el segundo aspecto que es optar para repartir nuestros recursos para satisfacer al maximo posible nuestras necesidades; Cuando estos recursos no alcanzan para lograr el 
objetivo aparece el problema denominado escasez.
Si fuera una situacion del individuo, la opcion estaria en como utilizar el ingreso(Producto del salario, o de la ganancia, de un prestamo o de un regalo o ganancia
de una loteria) 
Pero la escasez tambien se presenta en las decisiones empresarias: Voy a producir un bien u otro tipo de bien?;Debo emplear mas trabajadores o recurro a maquinas roboticas?
La escasez tambien aparece en las decisiones de gobierno: Invierto mas en edcucacion y menos en seguridad?, Como repartiremos el presupuesto Nacional?

Existen autores que dividen la economia en tres campos:

1 Economia Politica: Este item abarca determinados principios normativos, tales como los principios del liberalismo economico, los del socialismo, los
 del marxismo y otros.

2  Pensamiento Economico: Se lo entiende como la suma total de las opiniones y deseos consernientes a los sujetos economicos. Cuando dicho sujeto es el Estado (Nacional,
Provincial, Municipal) se establece lo que se conoce como politica economica, siendo esta la parte de la politica referida a la actividad del estado interviniendo
 en la economia de un pais para asegurar la adecuacion de los recursos escazos a los fines multiples.

3 Analisis Economico: Es algo independiente y objetivo, tratandose de un fuerte nucleo de tecnicas y herramientas gobernadas por patrones y reglas.

17/3/2022, 1:16â€¯p.â€¯m. - Franquito Ebner: What is Lorem Ipsum?
Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry's standard dummy text ever since the 1500s, when an unknown printer took a galley of type and scrambled it to make a type specimen book. It has survived not only five centuries, but also the leap into electronic typesetting, remaining essentially unchanged. It was popularised in the 1960s with the release of Letraset sheets containing Lorem Ipsum passages, and more recently with desktop publishing software like Aldus PageMaker including versions of Lorem Ipsum.

Why do we use it?
It is a long established fact that a reader will be distracted by the readable content of a page when looking at its layout. The point of using Lorem Ipsum is that it has a more-or-less normal distribution of letters, as opposed to using 'Content here, content here', making it look like readable English. Many desktop publishing packages and web page editors now use Lorem Ipsum as their default model text, and a search for 'lorem ipsum' will uncover many web sites still in their infancy. Various versions have evolved over the years, sometimes by accident, sometimes on purpose (injected humour and the like).


Where does it come from?
Contrary to popular belief, Lorem Ipsum is not simply random text. It has roots in a piece of classical Latin literature from 45 BC, making it over 2000 years old. Richard McClintock, a Latin professor at Hampden-Sydney College in Virginia, looked up one of the more obscure Latin words, consectetur, from a Lorem Ipsum passage, and going through the cites of the word in classical literature, discovered the undoubtable source. Lorem Ipsum comes from sections 1.10.32 and 1.10.33 of "de Finibus Bonorum et Malorum" (The Extremes of Good and Evil) by Cicero, written in 45 BC. This book is a treatise on the theory of ethics, very popular during the Renaissance. The first line of Lorem Ipsum, "Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet..", comes from a line in section 1.10.32.

The standard chunk of Lorem Ipsum used since the 1500s is reproduced below for those interested. Sections 1.10.32 and 1.10.33 from "de Finibus Bonorum et Malorum" by Cicero are also reproduced in their exact original form, accompanied by English versions from the 1914 translation by H. Rackham.

Where can I get some?
There are many variations of passages of Lorem Ipsum available, but the majority have suffered alteration in some form, by injected humour, or randomised words which don't look even slightly believable. If you are going to use a passage of Lorem Ipsum, you need to be sure there isn't anything embarrassing hidden in the middle of text. All the Lorem Ipsum generators on the Internet tend to repeat predefined chunks as necessary, making this the first true generator on the Internet. It uses a dictionary of over 200 Latin words, combined with a handful of model sentence structures, to generate Lorem Ipsum which looks reasonable. The generated Lorem Ipsum is therefore always free from repetition, injected humour, or non-characteristic words etc.

19/4/2022, 10:15â€¯p.â€¯m. - Pupi: *Condicionales*
0: Afirmacion 
Present simple + present simple
1: Prediccion
Present simple + will
2: Hipotetico
Pasado + would

*Adjetivos*
-ed: Esta persona esta...
-ing: Esto es...

*Vocabulario*
Raise money
Hold a sale
Jump a queue
Watch a programme
Do experiments
Cut hair
Get a seat
/////////////////////////////////
Infinitvo + off/on/down/up/over

_Ejemplos_
Click on
Click off
Take on
Take off
Put on
Put off
Scroll down
Scroll over
Dress up
Dress down
Log on
Log off
Got on
Got off
Went off
Went on

COSAS BASICAS
Definiciones:
LibrerÃ­a: Es un archivo importable que estÃ¡ escrito en un lenguaje determinado que proporciona distintas funcionalidades
Framework: Es un entorno de trabajo que otorga una estructura base con sus respectivas herramientas para la elaboraciÃ³n de un programa y/o el desarrollo de un software
Software: Son los programas que hacen posibles el funcionamiento de un dispositivo
POO (ProgramaciÃ³n orientada a objetos): Trabaja con clases y objetos
-	Clase: Plantilla para crear objetos
-	Objeto: Instancia de una clase 
La POO se inventÃ³ para hacer un cÃ³digo mÃ¡s legible, y rÃ¡pido de realizar, evitando una secuencia de ifâ€™s llamada â€œSecuencia espaguetiâ€

LIBRERIAS
Unas breves descripciones
pyenv: Permite cambiar fÃ¡cilmente entre varias versiones de Python
pipenv: Permite crear entornos virtuales
black: Ordena el cÃ³digo y lo hace mÃ¡s bonito a la vista
isort: Ordena el cÃ³digo alfabÃ©ticamente dicho en la programaciÃ³n
pytest: Herramienta para hacer pruebas automÃ¡ticamente y no manualmente

Codigos importantes
pyenv:
-	pyenv install â€¦ (Instalas una versiÃ³n de Python, ejemplo: 3.8.10)
-	pyenv global â€¦ (Vas a esa versiÃ³n instalada)
pipenv:
-	pipenv install â€¦ (Creas un entorno virtual en una versiÃ³n distinta)
-	pipenv Shell (Entras en ese entorno virtual)

Como funciona
pytest: TenÃ©s que crear un archivo aparte en donde crees un programa â€œespecialâ€ para poder ejecutar un test y probar si tu programa en tu archivo principal funciona correctamente

30/3/2023, 8:58â€¯p.â€¯m. - Franquito Ebner: Eso
30/3/2023, 9:12â€¯p.â€¯m. - BALL: Sure, I can help with that. English has several verb tenses, each used to indicate a different time frame or aspect of an action or event. Here are some of the most common verb tenses in English with examples:

Present Simple Tense: Used for actions that are happening now or that happen regularly.
Example: I walk to work every day.

Present Continuous Tense: Used for actions that are happening now, but may not be permanent.
Example: I am studying English at the moment.

Present Perfect Tense: Used for actions that started in the past and continue up to the present, or actions that happened in the past and have a connection to the present.
Example: I have lived in New York for five years.

Past Simple Tense: Used for actions that happened in the past and are now completed.
Example: I visited my grandparents last week.

Past Continuous Tense: Used for actions that were happening at a specific time in the past.
Example: I was studying when my friend called.

Past Perfect Tense: Used for actions that happened before another action in the past.
Example: I had finished my homework before I went to bed.

Future Simple Tense: Used for actions that will happen in the future.
Example: I will visit my friend next week.

Future Continuous Tense: Used for actions that will be happening at a specific time in the future.
Example: I will be studying at this time tomorrow.

Future Perfect Tense: Used for actions that will have been completed at a specific time in the future.
Example: I will have finished my project by next Friday.

I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any questions.
